article.headline: Arizona 83, Louisiana Tech 67
article.story: TUCSON, Ariz. -- Nic Wise scored 24 points and Jamelle Horne added 20 points and eight rebounds as Arizona defeated Louisiana Tech 83-67 on Wednesday night. Five players scored in double figures for the Wildcats (4-4), who snapped a three-game losing streak. Kyle Gibson finished with a game-high 25 points for Louisiana Tech (7-2), and DeAndre Brown added 13. Arizona, which led 35-31 at halftime, went on a 12-4 run to start the second half. Derrick Williams scored seven points during the spree and gave the Wildcats a 51-35 lead with put-back dunk. The closest Louisiana Tech got after that was 55-45 with 10:10 remaining.
